Package: infuse
Type: Package
Title: Net Treatment Benefit and Win Ratio Statistics Using Influence Functions
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "Alberto", "Alvarez-Iglesias",
      email = "alberto.alvarez-iglesias@universityofgalway.ie",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: A comprehensive framework for Net Treatment Benefit and Win 
    Ratio statistics using an intuitive 'Sow-Harvest-Reap' workflow. The package 
    provides tools to 'sow' data by preprocessing survival, continuous, 
    and binary outcomes with support for Generalized Pareto Distribution 
    (GPD) tail extensions. It 'harvests' point estimates and 
    observation-level influence functions for favorable and unfavorable metrics
    via a high-performance C++ engine. 
    Finally, it 'reaps' statistical inference (standard errors, 
    confidence intervals, and p-values) and supports Non-Prioritized 
    Outcome (NPO) synthesis through weighted influence function 
    aggregation. This approach specifically accounts for the covariance 
    between multiple endpoints and provides robust variance estimation in 
    the presence of censoring.
